inferred MHC restriction evidence

definition.value: Evidence about the restriction of some MHC protein complex that is bound to some epitope.
Coordination between OBI and ECO is work-in-progress. In OBI, the inferred restriction is modelled as a 'conclusion based on data'.

label.value: inferred MHC restriction based on traceable author statement

definition.value: An inferred MHC restriction determined by an author's statement that the restriction of the epitope was already known prior to their publication.

label.value: inferred MHC restriction based on MHC ligand assay

definition.value: An inferred MHC restriction determined by a positive outcome in a MHC ligand assay.

label.value: inferred MHC restriction based on single MHC available in T cell assay

definition.value: An inferred MHC restriction determined by a positive outcome in a T cell assay where the antigen presenting cell (or tetramer/multimer) expressed only a single MHC molecule.

label.value: inferred MHC restriction based on set of MHC  available in T cell assay

definition.value: An inferred MHC restriction determined by the reduction or loss of a positive outcome in a T cell assay when subsets of MHC bearing APC were blocked.

label.value: inferred MHC restriction based on pattern of reactivity of same T cells with different MHC in T cell assay

definition.value: An inferred MHC restriction determined by a positive outcome in a T cell assay when APC expressing specific MHC were used and a negative response with APC not expressing the specific MHC.

label.value: inferred MHC restriction based on type of effector T cell utilized in T cell assay

definition.value: An inferred MHC restriction determined by a positive outcome in a T cell assay using specific T cell subsets as effector cells or by a negative outcome when a spceific subset is blocked by antibodies.

label.value: inferred MHC restriction based on type of biological process measured in T cell assay

definition.value: An inferred MHC restriction determined by a positive outcome in a T cell assay where the response  measured is indicative of a certain T cell subset.

label.value: inferred MHC restriction based on pattern of donor reactivity with different MHC in T cell assay

definition.value: An inferred MHC restriction determined by the association of a positive outcome in a T cell assay with the presence of certain alleles within the responding population.

label.value: inferred MHC restriction based on MHC binding prediction

definition.value: An inferred MHC restriction determined by predictive analysis of the epitope-MHC interaction, based upon the sequence or structure of the epitope without experimental assay.
